<br>
tstaff 29/30 = 0.96 how can 29 go into 30 less than 1 time? lol<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> /BONK</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Someone skipped a lesson on divisors, quotients, and dividends. To make things simpler, think of these as fractions.  <br>
37/36 is clearly more than one because 37 &gt; 36.<br>
29/30 is clearly less than 1 because 29 &lt; 30.<br>
<br>
I calculate 37/36 as 1.0277777 which rounds to 1.03<br>
I calculate 29/30 as 0.9666666 which rounds to 0.97<br>
<br>
While the Tranquil Staff's damage bonus is applied slightly more often, this does not totally neutralize the ratio difference.  <br>
<br>
Amygdalan War Staff ADVANTAGE:  It will put out more melée damage, has half the weight, is better for ripostes and damage shields, and it adds stats : 8Sta 8Dex 75HP.  hp rok.<br>
<br>
Tranquil Staff ADVANTAGE:  Every swing has a chance to nuke your foe for an irresistable 120 damage and stun it for up to 12 seconds, which many players use to melée the stunned mob from behind, avoiding any chance for the mob to dodge, parry, or riposte your swings for the duration of the stun.<br>
 <p>-Korph
