</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uddubois.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ddubois</A> at: 9/21/02 8:41:01 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uelfusab.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elfus AB</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/24/02 12:13:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11428.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Amy vs. TStaff</span><hr size=1> I hoped to come here and give people the comfort of knowing they chose the right weapon, because I too own both TStaff and Amy Staff and can tell you without a doubt that one of them is better than the other.<br>
<br>
Unfortunately, the one I have no doubt is best is the TStaff, so you still have disagreement even with the people who have both.<br>
<br>
I did no parses with it or any scifi testing. The difference in result was so huge, I saw no need to doubt it. The area I really looked for the TStaff/Amy Staff to perform was in taking out mobs such as Lodizal, Guardianwurms, Cliff Golems and any other lvl60ish money mob that is doable by a monk, shaman and cleric trio. I can tell you the difference in how much mana the cleric had left over after each fight.<br>
<br>
With the Amystaff fighting Lodizal (only melee) the cleric spent more time standing and healing and not medding. Although it was still a sure kill, the cleric finished the fight with 20 mana. Did this twice with Amystaff and same result pretty much on each time. Shaman  had Lodi slowed right off the bat and did same amount of DoTs.<br>
<br>
With the TStaff, the cleric finished the fight with 70 mana. To me, this is amazing. I mean, even if all it was was luck in the TStaff's favor, 70 mana compared to 20 mana is huge. <br>
<br>
Only did Lodi once with TStaff, but have done Guardianwurms many times using TStaff and one and a half with Amy Staff. Each time I tried GW's with Amystaff, I had doubts on if we would be able to win. The first time was very close. Cleric went OOM with GW at 10 percent and shaman had to canni and heal as fast as he can. Second time was even worse and I switched to TStaff because of that.<br>
<br>
With the TStaff, it was a sure fight each time. Ther is something to be said for stunning a mob right when he was about to quad you for 400s. No matter how much better stats and weight savings the Amystaff gives you, it does not give you a near unresistable stun proc. And yes, procs are a random thing of luck , but with 255 dex, luck seems to happen a lot. And to the people who say ther is a chance you can fight 10 fights or what have you, in a row and not have the TStaff proc once (obviously, you never owned a TStaff), well, ther is also a chance you can fight 10 fights in a row and not hit the mob once. Ther is a chance you can /random 1 100000 and have it hit 325 each time, ten times in a row. Ther is a chance Verant will release PoP on time, and the servers be up on time and everything works as planned, right from the start. <br>
<br>
I dont know about all the other chances, but I can tell you that even with just 150s dex, the TStaff procs a lot. With 255 dex, it procs a ton. And if all you do is use it to fight low blue mobs that hit for 120s and the fight only last a minute or 2, than a stun  won't be much of a factor and a better pure dmg stick might be the better choice ( Amy Staff even just as  pure dmg, is not that much better) . But when you are tanking mobs that hit 300 plus, stuns are FRIGGEN HUGE in how much damage you take, how many times cleric needs to heal and how well clerics mana pool will stay through the encounter. When you fight  mobs that have 20k plus hitpoints, hit in the 400s and you are it for tank and damage dealer, the fight will last a long time, you will proc your TStaff in the double digits easily and if even one of those stuns landed right when the mob was about to quad you in the 400s (even if the stun  last only a second), you just saved your cleric a complete heals worth of mana. Like I said, cleric at 20 mana when I use Amy, cleric at 70 mana when I use TStaff. Pretty clear to me which staff I will use.<br>
<br>
